## Supabase Storage — next/image

Add this to `next.config.ts` to allow images from Supabase Storage:

```ts
images: {
  remotePatterns: [
    {
      protocol: "https",
      hostname: "*.supabase.co",
      pathname: "/storage/v1/object/public/**",
    },
  ],
},
```

Always use `next/image` (not `<img>`) for Supabase Storage assets.

---

## Query pattern

```ts
"use server";
import { createClient } from "@/lib/supabase/server";

export async function getRecord(id: string) {
  const supabase = await createClient();

  const { data, error } = await supabase
    .from("your_table")
    .select("*")
    .eq("id", id)
    .maybeSingle();

  if (error) throw new Error(error.message);
  return data;
}
```

Always handle or surface `error`. Never silently discard it.

---

## Type safety

Generate database types with the Supabase CLI and commit them:

```bash
npx supabase gen types typescript --project-id <project-ref> > src/lib/supabase/database.types.ts
```

Pass the generated type to the client for fully typed queries:

```ts
import type { Database } from "@/lib/supabase/database.types";
createServerClient<Database>(url, key, { cookies: ... });
```

---

## Rules summary

- Use `@supabase/ssr` — never `@supabase/auth-helpers-nextjs`.
- Always `await createClient()` on the server; never `await` it on the browser.
- Import the server client in all server-side contexts; the browser client only in `"use client"` components.
- Never expose `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` to the browser or client components.
- Add session refresh middleware only when Supabase Auth is in use.
- Always throw or surface Supabase query errors — do not swallow them silently.
- Use `getUser()` server-side for auth checks, not `getSession()`.
